1956;;The Intimate Stranger;;British;;Richard Basehart;;Mary Murphy, Constance Cummings, Roger Livesey;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Intimate_Stranger_(1956_film);;Reggie Wilson's Hollywood career as a film editor ended after he had an affair with his boss's wife. He then moved to England, became successful and married the daughter of a producer . They are both working on a new film 'Eclipse'. His new life is threatened when he starts receiving intimate letters from a woman. She reminds him of a relationship they had some time ago but he genuinely has no knowledge of it . Has he a sick mind or is he the victim of an evil scheme?